Job Description:
OUC - The Reliable One, an industry leader and the second largest municipal utility in Florida committed to serving the community and the environment, is presently seeking a Business Applications Supervisor- Oracle CC&B to join the Digital & Technology division.

We are looking for a skilled information technology professional with knowledge of utility applications and experienced in supporting business operations to serve as a subject matter expert across the Customer Information System (CIS), Meter Data Management System (MDM), Bill Print and Prepaid systems. Seeking extensive business analysis and/or technical experience with Oracle Utilities database products (CC&B, MDM, and/or Head End System) and application framework.

In this role, you will be responsible for providing leadership, advisement, coordination, and oversight to all aspects of corporate, enterprise and resource planning applications, including but not limited to: client interface; system incident triage; solution development; release coordination; environment coordination; quality assurance coordination; product vendor interface; IT Operations interface; on-call support; staff development; and performance evaluations.

OUC’s mission is to provide exceptional value to our customers and community by delivering sustainable and reliable services and solutions. Click here to learn more about what we do.

The ideal candidate will have:

Bachelor’s Degree required. Information Technology, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Management Information Systems (MIS), or Business from an accredited college or university, other disciplines considered. In lieu of a degree, equivalent combination of education, certifications and experience may be substitutable.
Minimum of seven (7) years of progressive experience in providing analysis and support of business operations utilizing advanced business applications, to include:
Minimum of five (5) years in a role involving support, usage and configuration and/or development of CIS and/or other utility applications (e.g. CC&B, MDM, AMI) with three (3) of those years being actively involved with development and implementation; and/or Billing, Metering, AMI, Real-Time Payments and transactions.
Minimum of one (1) year of experience leading small/medium project and other improvement/enhancement efforts
Previous Supervisory experience (preferred)
Experience with Java, OUAF, ESB, APIs (preferred)
